// Metadata Manager
// Manages folder organization and lock state for diagrams and documents.

All metadata is persisted to a single JSON file (config.METADATA_FILE). State is kept in
memory and flushed synchronously after every mutating operation. The structure tracks a
list of folder names and a per-item map of { folder, locked }.

FUNCTION MetadataManager.initialize() -> void
  IF the metadata file exists, read and parse it into memory.
  On parse failure, fall back to an empty { folders: [], items: {} } structure.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.save() -> void
  Write the current in-memory metadata to the metadata file as formatted JSON.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.getMetadata() -> Metadata
  Return the entire in-memory metadata object.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.getItemMetadata(id) -> ItemMetadata
  Return the metadata for the given id, defaulting to { folder: null, locked: false }.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.setItemFolder(id, folder) -> void
  Throw if folder is non-null and doesn't exist. Create the item entry if needed,
  set its folder, and save.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.setItemLocked(id, locked) -> void
  Create the item entry if needed, set locked, and save.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.updateItem(id, updates) -> void
  Apply partial updates (folder and/or locked) to the item, validating that any
  non-null folder name exists. Save after applying changes.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.isLocked(id) -> boolean
  Return whether the item is locked, defaulting to false.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.createFolder(name) -> void
  Throw if folder already exists. Append name to the folders list and save.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.renameFolder(oldName, newName) -> void
  Throw if oldName not found or newName already exists. Update the folder in the list
  and update all items that reference the old name. Save.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.deleteFolder(name, moveItemsToRoot) -> void
  Throw if folder not found. IF items exist in the folder and moveItemsToRoot is false,
  throw. Otherwise move all items in the folder to null (root). Remove the folder and save.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.getFolders() -> string[]
  Return a copy of the folders list.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.getItemsInFolder(folder) -> string[]
  Return ids of all items whose folder matches the given value (including null for root).

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.removeItem(id) -> void
  IF the item exists, delete it and save.

---

FUNCTION MetadataManager.reset() -> void
  Reset in-memory state to empty. Call initialize() afterward for a new storage location.
